description:
//FOOD//
Chicken Katsu Volcano Plate: This dish does not come with curry! But instead comes with rice, miso soup, spinach salad with corn, and crispy breaded chicken on a bed of shredded cabbage. The miso soup came out first and it was steaming hot, perfect for a cold day! The chicken was well seasoned and crispy. There are bottles of Katsu sauce available if you want more! The cabbage was fresh and added a nice crunch! For ~$9 it was a delicious and filling meal!

Beef Curry, Medium Spicyness: It was spicier than anticipated! But the BF did not enjoy the rice very much, it did not taste fresh and it was not fluffy. It was a bit dry! A little disappointing, but drenching it in curry helped a bit. 

Potato Croquette: It is pretty much a flat fried ball of mashed potatoes. 

//AMBIANCE//
It's a meld of a fast food and a sit-in restaurant. It gets busy here! 

DO NOT sit in the table next to the wall and closest to the trash can and the door. There is a draft that blows in, you will be freezing! And your food will get cold faster! 

It can get really really busy! You might have to wait for a table because this place is popular!

//SERVICE//
There was only ONE waitress. And she was seating everyone and at the register taking orders and serving all of the customers and bussing all the tables and she did a great job! She was killing it! She was attentive! And she even let us change tables!  

//SUMMARY//
This is a great place for a quick meal that is warm filling and affordable!
